urface. Chemistry is\nessential for the ionization of hydrogen in these disks. The lack of a gap\nbetween the central objects and these disks suggests that they accrete through\nboundary-layer accretion. This would exclude the stars having a strong magnetic\nfield. Their structures suggest that both disks are transitional in nature,\nthat is to say they are in the process of being cleared, either through\nboundary-layer accretion, photo-evaporation, or through companion activity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Jan 2023 11:43:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-01"}
